                They were very surprised! They didn’t think that I would say yes, and they did not have a baptism set up. They were just wanting to feel me out so that they could figure out if I wanted to be baptized or not be baptized.


            </span>

            <span id="See_More_Mod"><a href="#" id="restofstoryb-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstoryb');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
            </span>

            <div id="restofstoryb" class="more">

                <span id="Second_Paragraph_Mod1" class="more">
                    They rushed out and arranged for a baptism on that day. The Relief Society President played the piano and another sister was the chorister. They called the Branch President and he was there, and another brother gave a talk. On that day I was baptized and I didn’t really know the difference that they really didn’t have that baptism set. <br /><br />

                    One of the outstanding attractions to the Church was the temple and the sealing powers that take place in the temple. To me, the temple was the all-encompassing, important part and difference between the Mormon Church and the Catholic Church. If there wasn’t the temple, I didn’t see any reason to join the Mormon Church.
                </span>
