            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">
            I think the happiest would have been when Teresa decided to be baptized. We had just been transferred to Little Rock, Arkansas, and after the first day at work I came home and there was a little Nash Rambler parked in front of the house. I walked in and there were two missionaries sitting on the sofa. “Whoa! She let ‘em in?” 
