           In 1966 we made an appointment to go to the temple and be sealed together. The branch was very helpful for us. The branch president let us borrow his car, which had an air conditioner, because he didn’t want us to drive all the way out to Idaho (1777 miles) with no air conditioner, because it was really, really hot. 
